ret:
To select the AF Mode before taking a picture, first ensure the lens focus mode switch is set to <AF> (as stated in Reference Doc 5). Then, set the camera Mode Dial to a Creative Zone mode (P, Tv, Av, M, or A-DEP) — in Basic Zone modes, AF mode is selected automatically and cannot be manually changed. In Creative Zone modes, you can choose among three AF modes: 
• One-Shot AF: for still subjects; 
• AI Servo AF: for moving subjects; 
• AI Focus AF: automatically switches from One-Shot to AI Servo if a still subject begins moving (Reference Docs 4 & 5). 
You can access and change the AF mode via the camera menu or quick control screen — press the <MENU/OK> button <PIC> and navigate to the AF mode setting. Note: AF point selection (manual vs. automatic) is separate but related — press the < > button and use the multi-controller to select an AF point <PIC>. , ["Manual29_24", "Manual29_8"]
